The defendant Antrell Darrian Taylor was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Endangering Safety by use of Dangerous Weapon w/ Controlled Substance, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 941.20(1)(bm).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Antrell Darrian Taylor in court with attorney Daniel E Meylink.  Joy Hammond and Alex Mueller appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  Jury panel in court at 9:07 am.  Closing arguments by state and defense.  Court charged the jury.  Alternate juror selected by lot and released.  Jury retired at the hour of 9:39 am to deliberate in the charge of Sheriff's Deputy Berlin who was duly sworn for that purpose.  At the hour of 11:01 am the jury returned and, by their foreperson, brought in a verdict of GUILTY which was then read.  Court polled and discharged the jury.  Verdict received and filed.  Court granted state's motion for judgment on the verdict and denied defense motion for judgment not withstanding the verdict.  Court ordered entry of judgment of conviction.  Court ordered case adjourned for sentencing in Branch 4.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for May 25, 2016 at 01:30 pm.

Jury list received and filed.    Court instructed jury.  Opening statements by state and defense.  Trial proceeded.  Sworn for the state:  Sgt. Cody Smith - Village of Shorewood Police Department. Exhibit 1 offered and received.  Jury out of box at 2:55 pm.  Court began colloquy with the defendant about his right to/not to testify.  Court finds the defendant knowingly, intelligently and voluntarily waives his right to remain silent and will testify.  Jury panel in box at 3:21 pm.  Sworn for the State:  Edward Oliver - Lab Analyst.  Exhibit 2 offered and received.  State rests subject to rebuttal.  Defense reserves right to any motions.  Sworn for the defense:  Antrell Taylor.  Defense rests.  State will call no rebuttal witnesses.  Jury out of box at 3:56 pm.  Defense motion for directed verdict at close of state's case denied by the court.  Jury instruction conference put on the record.  Jury in the box at 4:22 pm.  Testimony closed.  Court instructed jury.  Jury released at 4:41 pm  Case adjourned for continued jury trial in Branch 4.  Jury trial scheduled for May 3, 2016 at 09:00 am.
